{{Quote|What&mdash;what is this place? I can almost see the sky from here!|Zayne Carrick|<ref name="kotor3" />}}
'''Junk Junction''', sometimes referred to as just the '''Junction''', was a large junkyard in the [[Lower City]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Taris/Legends|Taris]]. Established on the site of a group of high-rise buildings that were demolished and never replaced, Junk Junction was a vast expanse of rubble, trash, and refuse. The [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|Arkanian Offshoots]] [[Jarael]] and [[Gorman Vandrayk|Gorman "Camper" Vandrayk]], after settling on Taris, chose Junk Junction as their new home. Jarael and Camper concealed their [[junk hauler]], [[The Last Resort (starship)|''The Last Resort'']], within Junk Junction using tents and awnings, disguising it as their house.

==Description==
{{Quote|Beautiful, ain't it?|Marn Hierogryph|<ref name="kotor3" />}}
One of the largest junkyards in the [[Lower City]] of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Taris/Legends|Taris]],<ref name="cswe">{{CSWECite|II|181|Junk Junction}}</ref> Junk Junction was a desolate expanse of trash, rubble, and waste, although it was not entirely uninhabited. The skyline of Junk Junction was dominated by large towers of trash, and although it was located below the open air of the [[Upper City]], one could almost see the Tarisian sky from Junk Junction. There were a few remaining intact buildings still poking out from the refuse. The area of Junk Junction was large enough, and the piles of trash high enough, to conceal an entire [[junk hauler]] vessel within the waste. Said junk hauler was [[The Last Resort (starship)|''The Last Resort'']], which masqueraded as the home of [[Arkanian Offshoot/Legends|Arkanian Offshoots]] [[Jarael]] and [[Gorman Vandrayk|Gorman "Camper" Vandrayk]].<ref name="kotor3" />

==History==
{{Quote|Used to be a grid of high-rises standing here. Somebody demolished them to make room for something else&mdash;then forgot to put up the something else. Now it's just the ''Junction''.|Marn Hierogryph|<ref name="kotor3" />}}
[[File:Last_Resort_Junk_Junction.jpg|thumb|left|250px|''The Last Resort'' rises from Junk Junction.]]
Junk Junction was once the site of a grid of high-rise buildings, although they were torn down to make room for something else&mdash;however, nothing was built to replace them, and Junk Junction was eventually established.<ref name="kotor3" /> By the end of the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]], Junk Junction was one of the largest junkyards on Taris. When the Arkanian Offshoots Jarael and Gorman "Camper" Vandrayk decided to settle on Taris, they chose to live in Junk Junction, because it was large and open enough to conceal their junk hauler, ''The Last Resort''.<ref name="cswe" /> Jarael and Camper set traps within the trash to deter visitors,<ref name="kotor3" /> and they disguised ''The Last Resort'' as their home, surrounding it with tents and awnings.<ref name="handbook">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic Handbook]]''</ref>

In [[3964 BBY]], [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Zayne Carrick]] was accused of [[Padawan Massacre|murdering]] four classmates and went on the run along with an accomplice, local [[Snivvian/Legends|Snivvian]] hood [[Marn Hierogryph]]. Hierogryph took Carrick to Junk Junction to meet with Camper, who had helped him ship criminal [[Zovius Mendu]] off the planet not long before. After brief hostilities with Jarael, who meant to protect the elderly Camper, Carrick and Hierogryph were spotlighted by a [[Taris Civil Authority]] [[Taris Civil Authority gunship|gunship]] that was tracking the fugitives. Carrick, Hierogryph, Jarael, and Camper escaped the [[Gunship/Legends|gunship]] by taking flight in ''The Last Resort'', leaving a large hole in the middle of Junk Junction.<ref name="kotor3" />

==Behind the scenes==
Junk Junction first appeared in [[Knights of the Old Republic 3|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 3]], a [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] written by [[John Jackson Miller]] and released in [[2006]].<ref name="kotor3" /> In [[2008]], Junk Junction was given an entry in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''.<ref name="cswe" />

